From 57309f0999dcb00a464930aab0b3c1065c1e37bd Mon Sep 17 00:00:00 2001
From: Zach Taylor <zctaylor.work@gmail.com>
Date: Wed, 27 May 2026 14:06:16 -0400
Subject: [PATCH 40/48] Add warp.prompt: plugin-contributed native prompt
 segments (oh-my-warp)

Lets a plugin push segments into Warp's native prompt chip row via
`warp.prompt.set([{ text, side?, tooltip? }])` / `warp.prompt.clear()`
(gated by the `ui` permission). Segments render as native chips after the
built-in ones; left-grouped first, then right-grouped.

The plugin host can't render synchronously on the UI thread, so the model is
push: the plugin computes segment text in JS and pushes it (e.g. from
terminal.onCommandFinished or a timer); a singleton PluginPromptModel caches it
keyed by plugin id, and every PromptDisplay observes it and re-renders.

- context_chips/plugin_prompt.rs: PluginPromptModel singleton + PromptSegment/PromptSide
- context_chips/display.rs: subscribe + append plugin chips (reusing render_udi_chip)
- lib.rs: register the singleton unconditionally (render path is feature-independent)
- plugin/{app_requests,app/mod,host/native/js_api/mod}.rs: warp.prompt API + SetPrompt relay
- workspace/view.rs: store pushed segments on the model

True right-edge alignment is a follow-up (the modern UDI prompt has no rprompt region).
